      "title": "Ollama Prompt Helper",
      "properties": {},
      "widgets_values": [
        "### 🌟 Star Ollama Prompt Helper - Quick Guide\n\nUsing the **Star Ollama Prompt Helper** is completely **optional, but highly recommended**. It takes your simple ideas and automatically expands them into rich, highly detailed prompts to get the absolute best results out of the generation models.\n\n#### What is Ollama?\n[Ollama](https://ollama.com/) is a powerful, free application that allows you to run Large Language Models (LLMs) completely offline and locally on your own hardware. It acts as the backend engine for this node.\n\n#### Prerequisites\nTo make this node work, you need to have the Ollama software installed and running in the background. \n*   📥 **Download Ollama here:** [www.ollama.com/download](https://ollama.com/download)\n\n#### Choosing a Model\nOnce Ollama is running on your machine:\n*   **Total Flexibility:** You can use *any* LLM model you have installed via Ollama. Just make sure the local address (usually `http://127.0.0.1:11434`) is correct.\n*   **Our Recommendation:** The model currently pre-selected in the node (`huihui_ai/gemma-4-abliterated:12b`) is a fantastic, tested choice and serves as a very strong baseline. However, feel free to pull and select your own favorite models!"
      ],
      "color": "#432",
      "bgcolor": "#653"
    },
